Trump established the White House Coronavirus Task Force on January 29, 2020.[557] Beginning in mid-March, Trump held a daily task force press conference, joined by medical experts and other administration officials,[558] sometimes disagreeing with them by promoting unproven treatments.[559] Trump was the main speaker at the briefings, where he praised his own response to the pandemic, frequently criticized rival presidential candidate Joe Biden, and denounced the press.[558][560] On March 16, he acknowledged for the first time that the pandemic was not under control and that months of disruption to daily lives and a recession might occur.[561] His repeated use of the terms "Chinese virus" and "China virus" to describe COVID-19 drew criticism from health experts.[562][563][564]
